\f0\fs26 \cf0 \cb2 Erik is a senior. I walked with him to and from the human interaction lab in the sociology building. Erik took time to stop for coffee at Coupa and say hi to friends, and made his way through the colonades in green and on the quad, because he likes their asthetic, and it makes him feel like he is experiencing stanford. He says he especially likes walking because it makes him feel like he is not letting Stanford's beauty pass him by. While we walked, Erik checked his texts and email. He said this makes his walks feel very productive. He also talked about the work he was doing in the lab. He said his time walking is good for reflection on his work or lectures, so he can better internalize it. He said his biggest gripe with walking is that he ends up travelling the same path again and again, so the sights become old. He would like an application that would suggest new alternative routes. I think it would also be good, since he is so interested in the stanford experience and the things he sees along the way, for him to be notified of the interesting spots on stanford in his vicinity that he may not know about.\
